    <p><strong>Restaurant furniture in India in 2026 costs anywhere from ₹800 per chair for basic stainless-steel canteen seating to ₹18,000+ per piece for upholstered designer chairs from premium manufacturers.</strong> The difference between a well-furnished 40-seater restaurant that looks sharp and one that looks like an afterthought often comes down to ₹2–4 lakh — not a fortune when spread across covers, but only if you buy smart. This guide covers every material, style, and price point available in India, with seating-density calculations, bulk-versus-single pricing, and a complete budget breakdown for 20-, 40-, and 80-seater restaurants.</p>

