      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the price of restaurant chairs in India in 2026? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Restaurant chair prices in India in 2026 range from ₹800 for a basic stainless steel chair to ₹18,000+ for a premium upholstered designer chair. The most common range for a mid-range casual dining restaurant is ₹2,500–₹6,000 per chair. Café chairs in popular metal and rattan styles typically cost ₹2,000–₹5,000 each.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How many covers (seats) can I fit in my restaurant? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">The standard industry formula for Indian restaurants is 14–18 sq ft of dining area per cover for casual dining, 18–22 sq ft for fine dining, and 10–14 sq ft for fast casual or café formats. Calculate your net dining area (excluding kitchen, toilets, and storage — typically 55–65% of total area), then divide by the sq ft per cover figure for your concept. A 700 sq ft dining area at 15 sq ft per cover gives you approximately 46 seats.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which furniture material is best for a restaurant in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For most mid-range Indian restaurants, solid wood chairs (sheesham or rubberwood) with a good commercial lacquer finish offer the best balance of aesthetics, durability, and cost. For cafés and trendy restaurants, powder-coated metal or PE rattan chairs work well. Upholstered chairs in commercial vinyl (not fabric) are ideal for casual dining restaurants that want a premium feel. For outdoor seating, use aluminium or HDPE/polypropylene — never use powder-coated mild steel or natural rattan outdoors in India.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the total furniture cost for a 40-seater restaurant in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A mid-range 40-seater restaurant in India should budget approximately ₹3,00,000–₹4,00,000 for a complete furniture set (chairs, tables, bar stools, and optional booth seating). Budget options can come in at ₹1,50,000–₹2,00,000 using SS or basic wood furniture. Premium upholstered setups can cost ₹5,00,000–₹8,00,000 for 40 covers. The cost per seat for mid-range furniture is typically ₹7,000–₹10,000 all-inclusive.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Where can I buy bulk restaurant furniture in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">The best options for buying bulk restaurant furniture in India are: (1) Local fabricators in industrial areas of Delhi (Okhla, Wazirpur), Mumbai (Kurla, Dharavi), or Bengaluru (Peenya) — best for custom dimensions and competitive pricing; (2) Godrej Interio and Featherlite for branded, consistent quality across multiple outlets; (3) Wholesale furniture markets like Kirti Nagar in Delhi for a wide range of options to compare in person; (4) B2B importers in major port cities for Chinese aluminium and PE rattan furniture. Always get at least 3 quotes and inspect a sample before committing to a bulk order.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What height bar stool should I buy for my restaurant? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">The correct bar stool seat height is 25–30 cm below your counter height. For a standard café counter at 90–100 cm height, you need a stool with a 60–65 cm seat height. For a full pub/bar counter at 105–115 cm, you need a 70–75 cm seat height. Always measure your specific counter before ordering — a 5 cm mismatch makes every customer uncomfortable. If you're still designing your space, a 90 cm counter with 65 cm stools is the most versatile and comfortable combination for a café or restaurant bar.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is rattan furniture suitable for outdoor restaurant seating in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Natural rattan is NOT suitable for outdoor use in India — it will soften, warp, and potentially develop mould within one monsoon season. However, synthetic PE (polyethylene) rattan is excellent for outdoor use. It looks nearly identical to natural rattan but is UV-stabilised, waterproof, and can last 8–12 years outdoors. Always specify "synthetic PE rattan" or "all-weather rattan" for outdoor seating — not "natural rattan" or "weather-resistant rattan."</div>
      </div>
    </div>

